@startuml seq-multi-instance
title Multi-Instance Sentinel Join

participant "Orchestrator\n(k8s HPA)" as ops
participant "Sentinel Instance 1\n(existing)" as inst1
participant "Sentinel Instance N\n(new)" as instN
participant "Vault" as vault
participant "Discovery API" as disc
participant "Redis\n(shared)" as redis
participant "SentinelRegistry\n(Blockchain)" as chain

note over ops
  Scale-out scenario: auto-scaler launches a new Sentinel pod.
  All instances share the same DID and the same private key
  (retrieved from Vault independently by each instance).
  No coordination between instances is required for auth.
end note

== New instance starts and bootstraps ==

ops -> instN: Launch pod (HPA scale-out event)

instN -> vault: Authenticate (K8s SA token)\nvault.auth.kubernetes.login(role="sentinel-prod-consumer-app")
vault --> instN: Vault token (TTL=1h)

instN -> vault: Read private key\nPath: secret/sentinel/prod/consumer-app/private_key
vault --> instN: private_key_bytes
instN -> instN: Compute DID → same DID as inst1\n(same key = same identity)

instN -> disc: GET /api/v1/config (mTLS)\nX-Sentinel-DID: did:key:z6Mk<SHARED_DID>
disc -> disc: Look up Sentinel by DID → ACTIVE
disc --> instN: 200 OK signed config bundle
instN -> instN: Verify config bundle → apply

instN -> redis: PING (test connectivity)
redis --> instN: PONG

instN -> disc: POST /api/v1/sentinels/heartbeat\n{ "did": "did:key:z6Mk<DID>",\n  "instance_id": "<uuid>",\n  "env": "prod" }
disc --> instN: 200 OK { "status": "ACTIVE" }

== Ready: Instance N starts handling requests ==

note over inst1, instN
  Both instances share:
  - Same DID (same identity)
  - Same private key (same signing capability)
  - Same Redis (shared JTI replay cache)
  
  JTI deduplication works correctly:
  A JTI seen by inst1 is in Redis;
  if the same token arrives at instN, Redis SETNX
  returns 0 (already exists) → rejected.
  
  No cross-instance coordination needed for VP verification.
  Each instance verifies independently.
end note

instN -> disc: Periodic config refresh (every CONF_REFRESH_INTERVAL)\nPeriodic status list refresh

note over chain
  SentinelRegistry records one entry per service DID,
  not per instance. Instance count is transparent to blockchain.
  The ACTIVE DID entry covers all N instances.
end note

@enduml
